President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Louisiana due to the COVID-19 pandemic. This declaration allows for Federal assistance to supplement State, tribal, and local recovery efforts. Federal funding is now available for Crisis Counseling for affected individuals in all areas of Louisiana. Additionally, funding is available for emergency protective measures and direct Federal assistance for all areas impacted by COVID-19 in Louisiana. George A. Robinson has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made in the future based on State requests and assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.